    <section>
        <h3 id="my-skill">Skills</h3>
        <hr>
        <p class="right" style="text-align: justify;">My Technical Skills
As a dedicated learner in the field of web development, I believe in building a foundation that is both strong and scalable. My technical toolkit is currently centered around the core technologies that power the modern web. I focus on writing clean, semantic, and efficient code to ensure that every project I work on is optimized for performance and user experience.
Mastering HTML (The Architecture)
I have achieved full proficiency in HTML (HyperText Markup Language), which I consider the backbone of any successful web project. My expertise includes working with semantic HTML5 elements, which not only help in structuring the content correctly but also play a vital role in SEO and accessibility. Understanding how to organize data, images, and links properly allows me to create a solid framework upon which beautiful designs can be built</p>
<p class="left" style="text-align: justify; background-color: #f0f0f0;">Mastering HTML (The Architecture)
I have achieved full proficiency in HTML <mark>(HyperText Markup Language)</mark>, which I consider the backbone of any successful web project. My expertise includes working with semantic HTML5 elements, which not only help in structuring the content correctly but also play a vital role in SEO and accessibility. Understanding how to organize data, images, and links properly allows me to create a solid framework upon which beautiful designs can be built.
Advancing in CSS (The Aesthetics)
Currently, I am deeply immersed in mastering CSS (Cascading Style Sheets). My goal is to transform basic HTML structures into visually stunning and highly interactive interfaces. I am learning how to control layouts, typography, and color schemes to create websites that are not just functional but also aesthetically pleasing. My focus is on understanding the CSS Box Model, positioning, and the art of making designs that adapt seamlessly to different screen sizes.</p>


